args:
The prince and friends try to take advantage of
their positional advantage in the Mistholt,
but Chelle anticipates the action. Hoping to
rally, the party targets Chelle's command post
directly, but she sees through this tactic as well
and turns the tables yet another time.
Over here, guys! The imperials shouldn't\nknow about this path—we'll take it and\nlink up with the boss.
What the hell? They cut around us!\nHow'd they even know about this path?!
Now, men! Offer up your very lives\nfor the glory of our lord!
Get ready, everyone! These Phobos units\nain't no joke, so fight hard or get dead!
More ill news, Highness. I fear the soldiers\nwe left behind to mount an ambush have\ninstead become victims OF an ambush.
Them Phobos guys are here, too.\nThey just kicked our tails all around the\nbattlefield—we barely got out alive.
They move as if they know every inch of\nthe forest, yet I cannot fathom they've had\nthe opportunity to conduct reconnaissance.
It's got to be Chelle. She probably had\nthe Mistholt thoroughly canvassed.

With those ＂cats＂ of hers, yeah?
Well, it's just one piece'a bad news after
the other. So what's the plan, boss?
There's gotta be some way outta this.
We need to stop my brother and sister\nfrom coordinating their forces.
Yes. They seem to be operating\nindependently at present; we\nwould do well to exploit that.
Alex, do you have any idea where\nChelle's command post is?
It is located near the Mistholt's edge.
And Leonidas's forces are currently\ntromping THROUGH the Mistholt...
Okay, here's the plan: Our main force will\nhit Chelle's army and draw the bulk of it\ninto the woods.
A bold plan—if a terrifically risky one.
I know it's dangerous, and I'm sorry.\nIf I saw any other way, I would take it.
You can apologize if we all end up dead.\nIt ain't needed now.
Hell, we've faced crap odds like this from\nday one, and we always come out on top!
The lunkhead's right! We're gonna win!
Chelle, it appurrs the army of the seventh\nscion has altered its movements.
Yes, it seems my little brother has taken\na VERY sudden interest in me.
And while I applaud the intention,\ndoes he truly think he can handle me?
He's clearly trying to weave through the\ngap between your army and Leonidas's.
Perhaps he assumes my brother and I\nare not coordinating our movements.
It is tiresome to be underestimated so.\nI must make him realize his folly!
Advance our forces. Bring our main army\ncloser to Leonidas.
You want us to move CLOSER to the\npurrince's army? Isn't that risky?
Only if you assume my brother and I\nare incapable of working together—\nwhich, I assure you, is not the case.
Chanzelia and Valkaheim have faced\nmutual enemies countless times.
And if my dear little brother believes he\ncan so easily sow chaos in our ranks,\nthe battle will be over before it can begin.
...I know we can't completely disrupt their\ntroops. Those two are more than capable\nof directing a joint force.
But if we can make them BELIEVE\nI think otherwise...
We can outfox the foxes!\nOh, but you ARE clever, darling!
I think the plan's working, man.\nI don't see any imperials here!
Yeah, but we still need to hurry and reach\nthe command post before our main force\nis surrounded.
It's just through here. If we take down\nChelle's base of operations, her entire\narmy will collapse!
Why are there so many soldiers here?\nShouldn't they be taking the bait?!
Did you think you'd outwitted me,\nBrother? Oh, but you are SO gullible.
Using your main force as a decoy is a bold\nmove, so I'll give you a gold star there.
Sadly, your little plan found its way to\nmy ears. It's all those curious little cats\nI warned you about before.
How did they possibly mobilize an army\nthis large without our being aware of it?
Forget the same rules, my dear—\nwe aren't even playing the same GAME.
Alas, I fear this is farewell.\nGoodbye, brother dearest.
Oh, and if you need to hate something,\nhate yourself for embracing an ideal that\nwas so far beyond you.
Harden your defenses, everyone!\nWe're going to get through this!
